{"sequence":74,"timestamp":"2026-04-26T15:42:28.641544928Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-36ae3fd9","body":"Finding summary: Review payloads that use only the new classified findings are rejected before the engine can queue them. In `src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs:230`, semantic validation still requires `follow_up_or_amendments` to be non-empty for every non-approved validation outcome. A `review` response with `classified_findings` populated, but the legacy string array empty, fails domain validation even though `src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs:163` defines `classified_findings` as the new classified finding channel and `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:8193` can queue those entries. Remediation hint: for `StageId::Review`, treat non-empty `classified_findings` as satisfying the non-approved follow-up requirement, and add a regression test with empty `follow_up_or_amendments` plus one classified finding.","dedup_key":"27c87b1da1ad2010bb13af1f49010f887b50b3f90dd583e1e03f74bdd2c3c726","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260426110147","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":75,"timestamp":"2026-04-26T15:42:28.658936436Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-4319474e","body":"Finding summary: The final-review classification enum is no longer backward compatible with persisted or in-flight payloads that use the previous kebab-case values. `src/contexts/workflow_composition/panel_contracts.rs:139` aliases final-review classifications to `ReviewFindingClass`, whose serde form in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:18` only accepts snake_case values. Existing final-review aggregates can contain `fix-now`, `planned-elsewhere`, or `propose-new-bead`; those now fail parsing in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:1088`, or are silently skipped in the reconstruction path at `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:1259`. Remediation hint: add serde aliases or a migration deserializer for the old values, and cover legacy aggregate/proposal parsing in tests, including legacy planned-elsewhere mappings.","dedup_key":"d172f86ae77cf5796ae39e76bf6e35b40940e10a3d0031ef2cf72ecb6a7e8b75","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260426110147","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
